subject: Add a class to handle RDE BEJ dictionary data
commitMessage:
Add a class to handle RDE BEJ dictionary data

This class is used to store RDE BEJ dictionary data transmitted
through bios-bmc circular buffer interface.

Signed-off-by: Kasun Athukorala <kasunath@google.com>
Change-Id: Idf7726a9f4647885ede615229d507f233ffb13c5

I'm thinking - would it make sense to perhaps separate out the RDE dictionary portion as a separate library? I'm actually not 100% sure how the split looks now that we have the BEJ as the separate repo / library so if there's not much code that goes in this repo, this is fine too

I am not sure putting this in another repo make sense since this is only used by RDE handler and RDE handler is used by the bios-bmc circular buffer.
 
When you said "separate" library, did you mean inside this same repo but use a separate static_library() call?

Sorry for the confusion, I meant within this repo, just a separate library as you said.

The split is easier if we split out the RDE part as a separate directory here - but again, depends on how much code / files you expect to be here
Yea thats a good idea. Checkout what I have right now. I created separate directories in include and src. I did not do it for the test directory.
minor nit: should we take out the "more"? as it's implicit in "add" that we'd add more
I kept it as "include", so that we can include the headers as "rde/header_1" rather than "header_1".
I've taken this out in my latest commit - feel free to rebase on top (and this change should go away)

I'm trying to figure out why we decrease this. Is it when we invalidate an already valid dictionary? If so, should we be covering this case in addMoreDictionaryData as well?

To avoid this, I wonder if we should have a helper function for updating validity. If we only update validity with the helper function, it'll automatically keep count of the dictionary count
Good idea. Added a 2 helper functions to validate and invalidate.
Maybe we should call this, validDictionaryCount to be easier to understand what this counter is for

what I meant above - should we check for if it was already valid and decrement the dictionary count?

What will the dictionary count be used for later?
If you did markDataComplete here, I think you'll see that we don't decrement the DictionaryCount I think which may be a bug
do you want `const std::span<const uint8_t>`? since you did it in the other change. I think they don't do anything, but should be consistent.
By other change, did you mean the libbej changes? That is a different repo. I'll remove the const in that.
as long as we're not expanding the span, I think we are fine to use const span <const > here

no need for std::span it should just work with `itemIt->second->data`.

If not, then try `{itemIt->second->data}`.
